                  <hi rend="small">THE </hi>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>ANCIENT
                                MARINER, <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <hi rend="small">A POET’S
                                    REVERIE.</hi>
               </titlePart>
            </docTitle>
            <lb/>
         </titlePage>
         <pb n="152"/>
         <pb n="153"/>
         <argument xml:id="ARGUrm">
            <head>
               <lb/>
               <lb/>
               <lb/>
               <lb/>
               <lb/>
               <emph>ARGUMENT. </emph>
            </head>
            <p>How a Ship, having first sailed to the Equator, was <lb/>driven by
                            Storms, to the cold Country towards the <lb/>South Pole ; how the
                            Ancient Mariner cruelly, and in<lb/>contempt of the laws of hospitality,
                            killed a Sea-bird ; <lb/>and how he was followed by many and strange
                            Judge-<lb/>ments ; and in what manner he came back to his
                            own<lb/>Country. </p>
         </argument>
